title.narrative: LEVERAGING MARKES FOR CHILDREN

description.narrative: UNICEF expands its leveraging of public, private and international financial resources and markets for children in MENA, in an innovative manner., which contributes to Child Poverty / Public Finance For Children, Children With Disabilities, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Social Protection. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: UNICEF demonstrates enhanced evidence-informed leadership and broadened partnerships to promote child rights and wellbeing across MENA.

description.narrative: In 2021, the Regional Office (RO) elevated the regional Public Finance for Children (PF4C) agenda, both internally and externally. Actions included conducting a high-level learning event on PF4C at the start of 2021, drafting guidelines on PF4C office-wide strategy and budget briefs, and building capacities at the country office (CO) level through training sessions. The RO also generated new evidence through a seminal study on PF4C in primary health care and a Social Expenditure Monitor with the Economic and Social Commission for Western Asia and the United Nations Development Programme.; | Status:Met | As-of Date:27/03/2022
